---
export const prerender = true;
import Gryphline from "../layouts/Gryphline.astro";
---
<Gryphline title="architecture">
  <section class="gl-shell">
    <p class="gl-kicker">case study · cloud engineering</p>
    <h1 class="gl-h1">how this ships<em>.</em></h1>
    <p class="gl-lede">
      Every piece of dram-soc.org lives in one Terraform state — the static site, the CDN,
      the DNS, the certificate, the contact form endpoint, and the log retention policies.
      <code>git push</code> triggers plan + apply. Total spend: <strong>~$4/month</strong> including
      cross-region failover, hourly Synthetics canaries, and Athena analytics.
    </p>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">01 · request path</h2>
      <div class="gl-panel">
        <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--tl"></span>
        <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--bl"></span>
        <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--br"></span>
        <pre class="diagram">
      user
       │
       ▼
   ┌─────────────┐        ┌────────────────┐
   │  cloudflare │        │   acm (us-east-1)│
   │     dns     │        │  wildcard cert   │
   └──────┬──────┘        └────────┬─────────┘
          │                        │
          ▼                        ▼
   ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │           cloudfront (us-west-2)         │
   │  · origin group (failover on 5xx/403)    │
   │  · viewer-request rewrite fn             │
   │  · security-headers policy               │
   └────┬─────────────────────────────┬───────┘
        │                             │
GET *   │                             │  POST /contact
        ▼                             ▼
 ┌──────────────┐             ┌────────────────┐
 │  s3 primary  │             │   http api v2  │
 │  us-west-2   │             │   api gateway  │
 └──────┬───────┘             └────────┬───────┘
        │ crr (async)                  │
        ▼                              ▼
 ┌──────────────┐             ┌────────────────┐
 │  s3 dr       │             │  lambda        │
 │  us-east-1   │             │  (node 20)     │
 └──────────────┘             └──┬────────┬────┘
                                 │        │
                                 ▼        ▼
                          ┌────────┐ ┌────────────┐
                          │  ses   │ │ dynamodb   │
                          │  send  │ │  audit     │
                          └────────┘ └────────────┘

  observability plane
  ────────────────────
  synthetics canary ─ 3 endpoints, hourly, us-west-2 ─▶ cloudwatch alarms
  x-ray tracing     ─ lambda + api gw + digest lambda ─▶ trace map
  eventbridge sched ─ nightly 03:00 utc               ─▶ digest lambda
     digest lambda  ─ cost explorer + synthetics + athena
                     ─▶ json → s3 (primary + dr) → /status /cost /insights
        </pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">02 · services + purpose</h2>
      <table class="gl-tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>s3</code></td><td>Origin bucket + DR replica + logs + Athena results.</td><td>Private, OAC-only reads. Cross-region replication → us-east-1 for 5-min RTO.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>cloudfront</code></td><td>HTTPS-terminating CDN + edge cache.</td><td>Origin group failover, security-headers policy, JS URL rewrite at the edge.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>acm</code></td><td>TLS cert (us-east-1 for CloudFront).</td><td>Free. DNS-01 validated via a Cloudflare CNAME.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>api gateway http v2</code></td><td>Public POST /contact endpoint.</td><td>Cheaper + faster than REST. CORS enforced at gateway (saves Lambda cost on preflights).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>lambda</code></td><td>Contact handler + nightly digest job.</td><td>Node 20 + X-Ray active tracing. IAM scoped to a single verified SES sender.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>ses</code></td><td>Sends contact submissions to the owner inbox.</td><td>Policy condition on <code>ses:FromAddress</code> prevents impersonation.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>dynamodb</code></td><td>Audit log of every submission + Terraform state lock.</td><td>Pay-per-request + PITR + encryption at rest.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>athena + glue</code></td><td>Serverless analytics over CloudFront logs.</td><td>Workgroup capped at 1 GB scanned per query. Saved queries as Terraform resources.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>synthetics</code></td><td>Puppeteer-based canary hitting 3 pages hourly.</td><td>Screenshots + timing + alarm on <code>SuccessPercent &lt; 100</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>x-ray</code></td><td>Distributed tracing across Lambda + API GW.</td><td>Free for first 100k traces/mo. Invaluable when the contact form breaks.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>eventbridge sched</code></td><td>Nightly cron for the digest Lambda.</td><td>Replaces CloudWatch Events. Cleaner IAM model.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>cost explorer + budgets</code></td><td>FinOps guardrails: 3 SNS thresholds + anomaly detection.</td><td>Anomaly monitor scoped to <code>&gt;= $1</code> daily drift; alerts to email.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>cloudwatch logs</code></td><td>Lambda + HTTP API access logs.</td><td>30-day retention on every log group — cost cannot creep.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">03 · monthly cost</h2>
      <table class="gl-tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th class="gl-tbl__num">$ / mo</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>cloudflare dns</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">0.00</td><td>Free tier, existing domain</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>cloudfront egress</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">~0.20</td><td>&lt; 10 GB/mo at portfolio scale</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>s3 storage + xfer</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">~0.10</td><td>Primary + DR ~30 MB × 2 + logs</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>cloudwatch logs</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">~0.50</td><td>30-day retention keeps this bounded</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>synthetics canary</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">~1.30</td><td>1 canary × hourly × single region</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>lambda / api gw / ddb / ses</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">0.00</td><td>All inside free tier at this volume</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>athena / glue</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">0.00</td><td>Catalog is free tier; queries in cents</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>acm cert</code></td><td class="gl-tbl__num">0.00</td><td>Free forever</td></tr>
          <tr class="gl-tbl__total"><td>Total</td><td class="gl-tbl__num">~2.10</td><td>Budget hard-capped at $25/mo</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">04 · CI/CD flow</h2>
      <ol class="ordered">
        <li><strong>Push to <code>main</code></strong> in the repo.</li>
        <li>GitHub Actions assumes an AWS IAM role via <strong>OIDC federation</strong> — zero long-lived credentials in the repo.</li>
        <li>Site change → <code>npm ci → astro build → aws s3 sync (primary + dr) → cloudfront invalidate /*</code>.</li>
        <li>Infra change → <code>terraform fmt → init → validate → plan</code> on PR; <code>apply</code> on merge to <code>main</code>.</li>
        <li>Both workflows use path filters — a doc-only change doesn't trigger a full redeploy.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">05 · deliberate choices</h2>
      <ul class="bul">
        <li><strong>Terraform, not CloudFormation.</strong> Broader job market, better plan output, multi-cloud portable.</li>
        <li><strong>HTTP API v2, not REST.</strong> ~70% cheaper. Contact form doesn't need REST-only features (usage plans, request validators).</li>
        <li><strong>Static Astro, not Next.js SSR.</strong> Site is 100% content — no reason to pay for warm Node servers per request.</li>
        <li><strong>OAC, not signed URLs.</strong> AWS-recommended path. SigV4 + full S3 feature support, unlike legacy OAI.</li>
        <li><strong>Origin-group failover, not Route 53 multi-region.</strong> Failover fires on first bad response instead of after health-check TTL — ~5-min RTO drops to ~30s.</li>
        <li><strong>Budget hard cap + Anomaly Detection, not "hope for the best."</strong> Bill can't exceed $25 without an email hitting the inbox first.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-panel gl-panel--elev cta">
      <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--tl"></span>
      <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--bl"></span>
      <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--br"></span>
      <p class="gl-kicker">code</p>
      <h2 class="gl-h2 cta__h">read the terraform</h2>
      <p class="gl-lede" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
        The full IaC lives at
        <a href="https://github.com/dram64/showcase.dram-soc.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          github.com/dram64/showcase.dram-soc.org
        </a> — <code>infra/</code> for Terraform, <code>site/</code> for the Astro source,
        <code>.github/workflows/</code> for the deploy pipeline.
      </p>
      <a class="gl-btn gl-btn--primary" href="https://github.com/dram64/showcase.dram-soc.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        github <span class="gl-btn__arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .diagram {
      font-family: var(--gl-mono);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      line-height: 1.4;
      color: var(--gl-ink-soft);
      margin: 0;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
    .ordered, .bul { padding-left: 20px; margin: 0; color: var(--gl-ink-soft); font-family: var(--gl-sans); }
    .ordered li, .bul li { margin-bottom: 12px; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 1rem; }
    .ordered code, .bul code {
      font-family: var(--gl-mono);
      color: var(--gl-cyan);
      background: var(--gl-cyan-soft);
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 2px;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
    }
    .cta { text-align: left; margin-top: 6vh; }
    .cta__h { margin-bottom: 16px; }
    @media (max-width: 700px) { .diagram { font-size: 0.6rem; } }
  </style>
</Gryphline>
